  "body": "**BUG REPORT**:\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n/sig auth\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nKubernetes distro testing v1.12.0-rc.2 shows in setups with self-hosted control planes (i.e. apiserver, controller-manager, scheduler run as pods) that previously worked on v1.11.3 and prior, the kube-controller-manager now crash loops with:\r\n\r\n```\r\nkubectl logs kube-controller-manager-66d694fd76-nj5sf -n kube-system\r\nW0923 04:05:46.836870       1 client_config.go:548] Neither --kubeconfig nor --master was specified.  Using the inClusterConfig.  This might not work.                                                            \r\nW0923 04:05:47.537843       1 authentication.go:246] Unable to get configmap/extension-apiserver-authentication in kube-system.  Usually fixed by 'kubectl create rolebinding -n kube-system ROLE_NAME --role=exten\r\nsion-apiserver-authentication-reader --serviceaccount=YOUR_NS:YOUR_SA'\r\nconfigmaps \"extension-apiserver-authentication\" is forbidden: User \"system:serviceaccount:kube-system:kube-controller-manager\" cannot get resource \"configmaps\" in API group \"\" in the namespace \"kube-system\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe kube-controller-manager is run with a [service account](https://github.com/poseidon/terraform-render-bootkube/blob/master/resources/manifests/kube-controller-manager.yaml#L74) with a [ClusterRoleBinding](https://github.com/poseidon/terraform-render-bootkube/blob/master/resources/manifests/kube-controller-manager-role-binding.yaml#L8) to the default system ClusterRole `system:kube-controller-manager`, which seems to be defined at https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/policy.go#L400\r\n\r\nEditing the ClusterRole manually to add `get` for `configmaps` was sufficient to fix the crash loop.\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ kubectl edit clusterrole system:kube-controller-manager\r\n...\r\n- apiGroups:\r\n  - \"\"\r\n  resources:\r\n  - endpoints\r\n  - namespaces\r\n  - secrets\r\n  - configmaps        <-- add me\r\n  - serviceaccounts\r\n  verbs:\r\n  - get\r\n```\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nI suspect a change between v1.11.3 and v1.12.0 release candidates altered kube-controller-manager to begin looking for configmap `extension-apiserver-authentication`, but didn't update the ClusterRoles. \r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\nRelease candidate testing is happening in https://github.com/poseidon/typhoon/pull/301\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n**Environment**:\r\n\r\n* Kubernetes version (use kubectl version): v1.12.0-rc.2\r\n* Cloud provider or hardware configuration: GCE, DigitalOcean, AWS\r\n* OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): Container Linux 1855.4.0\r\n* Kernel (e.g. uname -a): 4.14.67-coreos\r\n* Install tools: Typhoon\r\n",
